                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15053961" author="snazy" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2015 02:10:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stamhankar999&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stamhankar999&quot;&gt;stamhankar999&lt;/a&gt;, not everybody in the C* community is a native english speaker. Mind correcting the mistakes in the doc and provide a patch for it? Contributions are always welcome!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15054169" author="stamhankar999" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2015 09:02:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that&apos;s what I figured. Please do assign it to me and I&apos;ll try and take care of it sometime next week.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15054334" author="snazy" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2015 14:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, go ahead &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15058639" author="stamhankar999" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 19:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I came up with this list of outstanding questions while reading through the doc:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.1.4 - For 0x01 flag, the last sentence says &#8220;This is optional, and if not present, values will be bound by position&#8221;. I feel like the prior sentences imply this and it&#8217;s redundant.&lt;br/&gt;
4.1.4 - For the 0x20 flag, there is a sentence starting with &#8220;If provided, ...&#8221; which implies to me that you can have this flag set and &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; provide a timestamp. Is that true? If not, I&#8217;d like to take away the &#8220;If provided&#8221; part of the sentence.&lt;br/&gt;
Same for flags in 4.1.7.&lt;br/&gt;
4.2.2 - talks about a CREDENTIALS message. Does it mean AUTH_RESPONSE?&lt;br/&gt;
6.20 - do we mean v4 protocol serialization format?&lt;br/&gt;
7 - same question about serialization format.&lt;br/&gt;
9 - For 0x0100, does this happen when all auth challenges fail?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15058643" author="stamhankar999" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 19:42:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s my patch file. Let me know if you need anything else.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15058831" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 21:12:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stamhankar999&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stamhankar999&quot;&gt;stamhankar999&lt;/a&gt; does your patch include updates for your previous outstanding questions? (4.1.4 - For 0x01 flag..., etc.) Do those still need to be looked at by someone?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15058893" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 21:47:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A very quick scan of the patch looks like some nice language fixes, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15058992" author="stamhankar999" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 22:31:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I didn&apos;t make any assumptions regarding the answers to the outstanding questions, so I didn&apos;t change the text for those.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I didn&apos;t try this, but I presumed the process was that I was supposed to submit a patch, as opposed to trying to commit/push a branch and then submitting a PR. I&apos;d be happy to go the push/PR route, assuming I have the appropriate permissions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15059043" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2015 22:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches are preferred, so this is perfect. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15062395" author="stamhankar999" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 17:37:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;About my outstanding questions: will the reviewer update the doc to answer those, or answer here (and I&apos;ll update the doc accordingly and submit a new patch)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15066579" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 21 Dec 2015 15:34:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;About my outstanding questions&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I incorporated those in the commit directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
